@node Desc "Description"

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%                          Description                             %
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

DuraMembers is a membership tracking program for DLG.

Requires DLG Professional v1.0 and AmigaDOS 2.0+

@endnode

@node Install "Installation"

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%                           Installation                           %
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%


Create a directory called 'DOORS:DuraMembers' then create another
directory within this one called 'Text'.  Copy the included text
files to this 'Text' directory.

DuraMembers can be placed anywhere you want.  It creates 2 datafiles
in the DOORS:DuraMembers directory.

Add DuraMembers to your Crontab to run at midnight everday.  See @{" Update " link Update}
for an example Crontab entry.

To use the online CONFIG mode add the following menu item to any menu:

[ 1] Letter:                   *
[ 2] Executable: (path/name)   DOORS:DuraMembers/DuraMembers CONFIG
[ 4] Description:              Membership
[ 5] Type:                     Executable
[10] Load type:                OVERLAY
[12] Pend messages:            YES
[13] Cli mode:                 NO
[14] Pause on completion:      NO
[17] Priority:                 DEFAULT


DuraMembers uses templates to update user stats.  These are the same
templates that DLG uses for the User Editor.  You may want to create
some templates for the different membership plans you have available.
(ie. higher user levels, better ratios, etc...)

@endnode

@node Usage "Usage"

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%                             Usage                                %
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%


Usage: DuraMembers Config/S,Update/S,List/S,N=Name/K


                               @{" CONFIG " link Config}
                               @{" UPDATE " link Update}
                               @{"  LIST  " link List}

@endnode

@node Config "DuraMembers Config"

                             CONFIG
                             ~~~~~~

            This option can only be used while online

                          @{" Add Member      " link ConfigADD}
                          @{" Delete Member   " link ConfigDEL}
                          @{" Edit Member     " link ConfigEDIT}
                          @{" Global Add Days " link ConfigGLOBAL}
                          @{" List Members    " link List}
                          @{" Update Members  " link Update}

@endnode

@node Update "DuraMembers Update"

                             UPDATE
                             ~~~~~~

This option will scan through all the current members and update their
membership status (ie. Days Left).  Set DuraMembers to run at midnight
every night from your CRONTAB using this option.

Example CRONTAB entry: 0 0 * * * DOORS:DuraMembers/DuraMembers UPDATE

DuraMembers keeps track of the last time it updated the members' stats
therefore there's no harm if the UPDATE mode was ran twice in the same
day.  Also, if it didn't process at midnight (for whatever reason) it
will realize this the next time it's ran and will adjust stats
accordingly.

DuraMembers will not expire a user while they are online.  If a user
is online while they membership is expiring then the text file
'ExpError.TXT' will be sent to Sysop.  You will have to manually expire
the user by using 'DuraMembers Update' while the user is not online.

@endnode

@node List "DuraMembers List"

                             LIST
                             ~~~~

Lists all members; showing the expiry date , # of days left and the plan
they belong to.  Can be used from CLI or online.  It's also available
from within Config.


CLI Usage: DuraMembers LIST N=Name/K

If a username is provided then the membership stats for that member
will be displayed instead of the full listing.  This is useful for the
Login.DLGBatch or from a menu so members will always know when their
membership expires.  (ie. DuraMembers LIST NAME "%NAME")

If the user is not a member then the program won't do anything.  The
next version may allow a text file to be shown to the user (describing
the membership plans available, how to become a member, etc.)

@endnode

@node ConfigADD "Config: Add Member"

                 ADD A USER TO MEMBERSHIP


- Inputs required -

      UserName:  uses DLG's "guess-mode"
          Plan:  If you setup plans in your config file then you will
                 be prompted for the plan number to use for this user and
                 the amount of money they sent in.  If you want to
                 manually set the number of days/months then just press
                 return at this prompt.
   # of Months:  # of months until membership expires.
     # of Days:  # of days left until membership expires.
 Specific Date:  Use this to input an exact expiry date
Apply Template:  Select a template from the list to be applied to the
                 user while they are a member.

                 You will be asked if you only want to apply the upgraded
                 attributes from the template.


The user cannot be online while they are being added since DLG may not
recognize the new user information.  The program will notify you if this
is the case.  If the user is already a member then the program will
switch you into @{" edit " link ConfigEDIT} mode.

The user's original data file will be renamed to "User.data.old".  Do NOT
delete this file or else DuraMembers will not be able to restore the user's
stats when membership expires.

The user's Global File/Msg scan areas will be updated to include any new
areas they have access to.

Also, an entry in the user's notes will be added showing the expiry date
and number of days left.  This entry will be updated if the number of days
or the expiry date change.

@endnode

@node ConfigDEL "Config: Delete Member"

                 REMOVE A USER FROM MEMBERSHIP

Only input required is the member's name.  This will restore the user's
stats back to original (before they became a member).  Their Global Scan
File/Msg areas will also be updated to remove any areas they no longer
have access to.

Note: Only the user data fields that were upgraded (when the member was
      added) will be downgraded when deleted/expired.  (Ie. If the user
      changes their password/screen length/etc while they are a member,
      these settings will not be restored to the pre-member settings.
      This way they don't have to re-do any settings that were changed
      while they were a member).

@endnode

@node ConfigEDIT "Config: Edit Member"

                 EDIT MEMBER'S STATS


Sample Screen Output:

                    UserName: David Letterman
          [1] # of Days Left: 38
          [2]           Plan: Gold Plan
          [3]    Expiry Date: Tue  1 Aug 95
          [4]    Date Joined: Mon  1 May 95
          [5]   Last Updated: Sun 25 Jun 95

          [A] Add Days     [M] Add Months
          [Q] Quit/Save    [Z] Abort

Options 1 and 3 allow you to change the expiry date.  When changing the # of
days left, the expiry date will also change accordingly (and vice versa).

Option 2 is the current plan the member belongs to (if any).  No message
will be sent to the member if this is the only field you change.

Option 4 is the date the user became a member.  The program only uses this
field when the member is added.  You can use it for whatever you want after
that.

Option 5 shows the date that this member was last updated on (Update Mode).
This field should never be changed unless you know what you are doing.  I
only included it because I needed it for testing purposes and decided to
leave it there in the event that a problem is later detected.

[A] and [M] allow you to add a set number of days/months to this member's
expiry date.  You can use a negative number to subtract a set number of
days/months.  If subtracting days/months causes the # of days left to be
less than 1, # of days left will be set to 1 (you can't have a negative
# of days left).

[Q] will save any changes you have made and exit back to Config's main menu.
If stats were changed then "MemChanged.TXT" will be sent to the member.

[Z] will exit back to Config's main menu without saving any changes you
made.  "MemChanged.TXT" will not be sent to member.

@endnode

@node ConfigGLOBAL "Config: Global Add Days"

                 GLOBALLY ADD/SUBTRACT # OF DAYS


This command allows you to globally add or subtract days from all
your members accounts.

To subtract days from all acounts, use a negative number.

MemChanged.TXT file will be sent to all users, informing them of
their new expiry date.

@endnode

@node ConfigFile "Configuration File"

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%                        Configuration File                        %
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

Config file is called DuraMembers.CFG and resides in
DOORS:DuraMembers/.  Example config file included with this archive.

Here are the commands available in the config file:

LOGFILE     If you want a logfile kept then use this command to
            specify the filename for it.  If you don't want a logfile
            kept then omit this command.
            [ie. LOGFILE LOGS:DuraMembers.LOG]

LOGLEVEL    There are currently 4 loglevels available.  Ranging from
            0 (Terse) to 3 (Verbose) [Default: 1]

            0 = Record whenever a user is added, deleted, edited
            1 = Same as above except more information is provided
                (ie. Expiry date and days left) [Default setting]
            2 = Same as above but also records whenever a user is
                updated (ie. Daily maintenance)
            3 = Same as above but also records whenever this program
                is executed

For setting up membership plans, the following commands are available:

PLAN        Name of the plan [Max 30 chars]

NUMBER      ID Number of the plan.  DuraMembers requires this to keep
            track of which members are on which plan

COST        Cost for this plan [Ie. 15.95]

MONTHS      Number of months that will be added for this plan (for the
            amount specified in COST)

DAYS        Number of days that will be added for this plan (for the
            amount specified in COST).  You can only specify either
            DAYS or MONTHS, not both.

TEMPLATE    Template to use for this plan.  Put just the template name
            here.  No need to specify the path, also, the extension
            .template will automatically be added.
            [Ie. best_plan will become DLGConfig:Template/best_plan.template]


You can setup as many plans as you want.  DuraMembers uses the plan's
NUMBER to figure out which plan a member belongs to so don't reuse a NUMBER
for another plan unless there are no members belonging to that plan (unless
you want all those members to belong to the new plan).

@endnode

@node TXTFiles "Text Files Used"

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%                  Text Files Used by DuraMembers                  %
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%


The text files DuraMembers uses should be placed in
'DOORS:DuraMembers/Text/'.

Switches can be embedded into these text files (see below).

NewMember.TXT  - Sent to user when added to membership
DelMember.TXT  - Sent to user when removed from membership
                 (Delete command in Config mode)
MemExpired.TXT - Sent to user when memberhip has expired
MemChanged.TXT - Sent to user when their membership is edited
                 (Including when you globally add days)
ExpError.TXT   - Sent to sysop when DuraMembers tries to expire a user
                 while they are online.  (Do not use DLG switches in
                 this text file)

<# of days>DaysLeft.TXT - When updating the members number of days
                          left, it will check if this file exists.
                          If so, text will be sent to user.
                          (ie. 10DaysLeft.TXT would be sent to users
                           that have 10 days left)


If one of the above text files are being sent to a member that belongs to
a membership plan, then it will first try to find the corresponding file
with the extension '.<plan_number>.TXT'.  If it can't find this file then
it will default to the '.TXT' extension.

Ie.  If a user belongs to membership plan #2 and their membership expires,
     DuraMembers will first try to send <MemExpired.2.TXT>.  If it can't
     find this file then it will try <MemExpired.TXT>.

     If the above user is being updated and they have 30 days left then
     the program will first try <30DaysLeft.2.TXT> and if it can't find
     it will try <30DaysLeft.TXT>.


Switches that can be used within the above text files are:

%MEMBER       - Full member's name (must be used in ExpError.TXT)
%DAYS_LEFT    - Number of days left
%EXP_DATE     - Expiry Date [ie. Sun 05 May 95]
%JOINED       - Date user joined membership plan [ie. Sun 05 May 95]

Also, any of DLG's text switches can be used in these text files (except
for ExpError.TXT).

Example text files have been included in this archive.

@endnode

